You&#39;ll have to supply  more info. if we&#39;re to help.

&lt;aside&gt;Does WPOST let crawlers get content (Is there a robots.txt on 
this site that bars crawler access?)  Does the online policy explicitly 
bar robots?  The NYT policy seems to allow crawler access if the 
downloads are for personal use only.  Perhaps WPOST is the same.&lt;/aside&gt;

Back to debugging.  You can log in with your browser, right?  
Programmatic login by Heritrix is difficult to debug;  You could look in 
crawl logs to see whats happening on submission (Are you redirected, is 
it 200 on POST?) and in the ARC files to see what the login result pages 
you&#39;re getting back look like -- how do they compare to the browser 
pages?  You might try doing the login negotiation using CURL first -- 
because it&#39;ll be easier to follow the login vagaries in a tool like CURL 
-- to learn more about how it works before trying the login in Heritrix.

